            "flavorText": "The basidirond, also called a mindfrond, is a fungal creature that crawls about on woody tendrils. The large, bowl-shaped pod atop its body collects mineral-rich moisture--whether runoff from cave walls or fresh blood--for sustenance. It uses hallucinogenic spores to incapacitate prey long enough for it to beat its prey to a bloody pulp, then deposits the deliciously tenderized remains into this pod for consumption. A basidirond is over 6 feet tall and 3 to 4 feet wide, and weighs nearly 300 pounds when saturated.<br /><br />",
            "flavourText": "",
            "heritage": {
                "value": ""
            },
            "keyability": {
                "value": "str"
            },
            "level": {
                "min": 1,
                "value": "5"
            },
            "nethysUrl": "https://2e.aonprd.com/Monsters.aspx?ID=564",
            "recallKnowledgeText": "Recall Knowledge - Fungus : DC 20",
            "sidebarText": "<h3 class=\"title\"><img alt=\"Sidebar - Treasure and Rewards\" title=\"Sidebar - Treasure and Rewards\" style=\"height:20px; padding:2px 10px 0px 2px\" src=\"Images\\Icons\\Sidebar_5_TreasureAndRewards.png\"> Harvesting Spores</h3>The psychotropic spores of the basidirond can be harvested with a successful DC 20 Herbalism Lore or Nature check, yielding 1 dose of spores (1d4 doses on a critical success); on a critical failure, the basidirond creates a 10-foot-radius hallucinogenic cloud. Each dose is worth 10 gp for use in Crafting poisons, or 20 gp if the poison causes the @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Confused]{Confused} or @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Stupefied]{Stupefied} condition.",
            "source": {
